Desimartini Rising Students Club, FC Pune City enter Indian Women’s League football semis 
Rising Students Club and FC Pune City have entered the semifinals of the inaugural Indian Women’s League (IWL) football championship. football Updated: Feb 08, 2017 22:21 IST IANS Action from the Rising Students Club vs Jeppiaar IT FC match of the Indian Women’s League (IWL) football championship in Delhi on Wednesday. Rising won the match 7-0.(AIFF) 
Rising Students Club and FC Pune City reached the semifinals of the Indian Women’s League (IWL ) football championship following their wins over Jeppiaar IT FC (7-0) and Aizawl FC (4-0), respectively, at the Ambedkar Stadium in New Delhi on Wednesday. 
Rising Students sealed the top spot of the standings as they hammered seven goals past Jeppiaar IT to take their points tally to 12. 
Read more | Why India star Bala Devi missed the first woman’s football league 
Jabamani Tudu (68th, 69th, 76th and 90th minutes), Pyari Xaxa (28th, 42nd), Locahana Munda (32nd) were the scorers for Rising Students. 
FC Pune City finished fourth in the group stage with seven points in five matches, following their 4-0 win against bottom placed Aizawl FC. 
Aizawl FC did not amass any points in their maiden Indian Women’s League campaign, suffering five defeats in five matches. 
Roja Devi (19th minute), Laura Estibeiro (31st), Dalima Chhibber and 12-year-old Senorita scored in the dying minutes of the match for Pune. tags
